    "In 1960 Roberts retired, returning briefly to New York to be the first director of the State Council of the Arts, 1960-61, before moving back to Europe, living in Venice, Paris and London.": [],
    "In 1967 Roberts published his <em>Connoisseur's Guide to Japanese Museums</em>.": [],
    "His <em>Dictionary of Japanese Artists</em> appeared in 1976, which remains an influential resource for artists biography of Japan.": [],
    "Roberts moved to Baltimore in 1988 where he died fourteen years later at 95.": [],
